This paper deals with photorealistic style transfer, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques. The use of wavelet transforms is a key component of the proposed method, which falls under graphics (cs.GR) and signal processing (cs.MM) subfields. The paper also discusses the statistical properties of VGG feature space, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
